    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Skewed residuals and outliers in a linear regression model can certainly be a problem, as they violate the assumption of normally distributed errors. You can try a few things, like transforming your dependent variable (housing price) using a log or square root transformation. If the outliers are truly extreme, you might consider winsorizing them or using a robust regression method that is less sensitive to those large deviations. Remember, sometimes the data just isn't perfectly normal, and if the model fits well otherwise, you might proceed with caution.",
